channel.title: Photoshop problems?
channel.description:
Alright well a few days ago i activated my photoshop cs3 extended with a keygen and all worked out. Then about 2 hours into making a sig...it froze causing me to loose my work. It would then freeze over and over again whenever i tried to use free transform and apply it...So i uninstalled it. And now i try and reinstall it by redownloading it off the site then going through the setup. And it goes through the installation, and when its done it says it failed to install photoshop cs3 and something else but installed the extensions or w.e. I cant figure out what the problem is. It is not blocked by any firewalls, could someone please help me?
Thanks, Avalanche

item.dc:creator: @xxlegitxx xxlegitxx
item.description:
@xxlegitxx wrote:

Avalanche:

the actuall file but its a .uif file and idk what to do with it

Like therealjdb said, magiciso can help you out:
http://www.magiciso.com/Setup_MagicISO.exe - WARNING!!! NOT VERIFIED!!! OMG!

Just install it, burn CS3 to a cd, then uninstall MagicISO. I hate having random programs on my computer that I never use.

And tbh, many CS3 programs are the same thing as CS2 or Macromedia * 8, with a few minor additions that they charge you a couple hundred bucks for. If that cracked version doesn’t work, try PS CS2.
